My lwl/lwr implementation is wrong. Let me derive the correct LE semantics. The issue: `lwl 3(base)` with bo=3 should load 4 bytes (all of them) since byte 3 is the MSB. Let me figure out the correct mapping:

{
  "analysis": "My lwl/lwr is incorrect. For LE MIPS: lwl at addr A loads bytes from A up to the next word boundary into the HIGH part of rt. The number of bytes loaded depends on alignment. For `lwl 3(0x100)`=addr 0x103: byte 0x103 is the MSB of the word, so lwl loads just that 1 byte into the high position. For `lwr 0(0x100)`=addr 0x100: loads bytes 0x100..0x103 (all 4). Let me derive the correct formulas by understanding the MIPS spec precisely.",
  "plan": "Derive and test correct LE lwl/lwr formulas. For LE: lwl loads the most-significant bytes, lwr the least-significant. lwl(addr) loads (4-bo) bytes? No. Let me work it out: lwl effective addr A, aligned word W at A&~3, bo=A&3. LE lwl loads bytes [A .. word_end] into high bytes of rt.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "node << 'TESTEOF'
const mem = {0x100:0x11, 0x101:0x22, 0x102:0x33, 0x103:0x44};
function r8(a){return mem[a]||0}
function r32(a){return (r8(a)|(r8(a+1)<<8)|(r8(a+2)<<16)|(r8(a+3)<<24))>>>0}
// LE MIPS spec:
// LWL: rt = (mem_word << shift) | (rt & mask)  -- loads high bytes
// For LE, LWL addr=A, bo=A&3:
//   loads bytes A..(A|3) into the HIGH part
//   shift = 24 - bo*8, and keeps low (bo*8) bits of rt
// Actually for LE: LWL shifts left by (3-bo)*8
function lwl(rt,a){
  const al=a&~3,bo=a&3,mv=r32(al);
  const sh=(3-bo)*8;
  const m = sh===0?0:((1<<sh)-1)>>>0; // bits to keep from rt
  return (((mv<<sh)>>>0) | (rt & m))>>>0;
}
// LWR for LE: shifts right by bo*8, keeps high bits of rt
function lwr(rt,a){
  const al=a&~3,bo=a&3,mv=r32(al);
  const sh=bo*8;
  const m = sh===0?0:(0xFFFFFFFF<<(32-sh))>>>0; // high bits to keep
  return (((mv>>>sh)) | (rt & m))>>>0;
}
let rt=0;
rt=lwl(rt,0x103); console.log('lwl 3:',rt.toString(16));
rt=lwr(rt,0x100); console.log('lwr 0:',rt.toString(16),'expect 44332211');
// Test other combos
rt=0; rt=lwl(rt,0x101); console.log('lwl 1:',rt.toString(16));
rt=lwr(rt,0x102); console.log('then lwr 2... (different pattern)');
TESTEOF
",
      "duration": 0.5
    }
  ]
}
